Scope of JS8Forms & Commstat
The name CommStat was just an afterthought, it was originally called JS8Forms but the functionality evolved to something more.
CommStat is just a short version of Communicating Status. I dont particularly care for the name but cant think of a better name.
The scope for JS8Forms / CommStat was to simply add some form capability to JS8Call by creating a form for users to use to send a
status update (SITREP) and a way to automatically decode the form data on the other end. So end to end forms could be used much like
FLDigi or Winlink.
As many projects do, JS8Forms suffered from scope creep where I and others kept coming up with additional features and concepts.
This is where CommStat comes in, we went from forms to aggregating incoming data into useful tables and creating methods of
redundancy. This essentially led to the final scope which is a higher level than where it started.
The idea was to create a JS8Call add on software tool that supports a 100% decentralized group communication platform (JS8Call) to
allow instantaneous ad hoc networks to be created in real time based on nothing more than a group name. The forms, the mapping, the
marquees broadcast and flash broadcasts are essentially just features that add value to the network .
All of the receive features in CommStat are on a 60 second update cycle.
The concepts and software are solely driven by the author Dan Hurd W5DMH .
JS8 Email
JS8 EMail
Currently JS8 EMail simply formats and transmits an email message via JS8Call that is processed by APRSIS
when it is gated into the APRS system. This is somewhat unreliable as a gating enabled JS8Call station must
hear your message and gate it for you.
Possible future state : CommStat will gate the message for you directly to the internet without using APRS,
however this gating will have to be done by another member in your group that is running the CommStat
software.
JS8 SMS
JS8 SMS
Currently JS8 EMail simply formats and transmits an SMS message via JS8Call that is processed by APRSIS when it is
gated into the APRS system. This is somewhat unreliable as a gating enabled JS8Call station must hear your message
and gate it for you. For your station to gate messages you will need to turn on the reporting function in JS8Call
SITREP
CommStat SITREP
The form below can be populated and it will automatically generate a unique incident code and apply your callsign and
grid to the report. This is transmitted as a string with numeric characters representing each of the selections in the form.
On the receiving end, the SITREP is reported in the SITREP window with colors representing the numbers received for
each of the SITREP selections.
Currently there is not an ACK function to the SITREP process..
Incoming SITREP
CommStat SITREP
This is transmitted as a string with numeric characters representing each of the selections in the form.
On the receiving end, the SITREP is reported in the SITREP window with colors representing the numbers received for each of the SITREP
selections.
The receive functions are on a 60 second refresh cycle so updates are not necessarily instantaneous
KD81B3: @GROUP ,EN83,1,8019,120000110,AFGHAN PULLOUT CREATES A DESTABILIZED TALIBAN GOV,{&%} ?
A typical string looks like this with callsign, group, grid, precedence, incident id number, sitrep status codes, message and message type identifier
Message type identifier
Incoming Data
INCOMING REPORT
This table automatically populates with received Directed Messages, these messages are all directed
messages even though they may not be directed to you or your group. This is updated once a minute and
maintains the last 1000 lines from the JS8Call DIRECTED.TXT FILE.
NET Check In
NET Check In
This feature allows you to check in to a group NET and the NCS running CommStat automatically records
your check in and adds your callsign to a group ACK sent after the check in time window . The expectation is
that the NCS can receive multiple check ins at the same time (overlapping freq notwithstanding) for the first
10 min of the NET, then the NCS can send a group ACK out to the members that have checked in.
You can choose to add traffic to the check in or leave it with the NOTRFC message
NET Check In Encoding
NET Check In
This feature allows you to check in to a group NET and the NCS running CommStat automatically records
your check in and adds your callsign to a group ACK sent after the check in time window . The expectation is
that the NCS can receive multiple check ins at the same time (overlapping freq notwithstanding) for the first
10 min of the NET, then the NCS can send a group ACK out to the members that have checked in.
You can choose to add traffic to the check in or leave it with the NOTRFC message
NET Check in transmitted string encoding :
Callsign group message or traffic message type identifier
KD8PGB: @AMRRON ,NOTRFC,{~%} ?
Member List
Member List
CommStat uses the DIRECTED.TXT file generated by JS8Call and will take group members callsigns, grids and last time
heard from that list and add them to the members list so you can quickly see who the members are.
Members are only listed if they are using the @GroupName in JS8Call
NET Roster
NET Roster
This feature will capture NET Check ins for adding to a NET report but more importantly it will include a Group Ack button, so
during a NET for the first 10 min the NCS can listen to multiple incoming signals and not worry about missing any while sending
acks.at the 15 min mark the NCS can send a Group Ack that has a list of the callsigns that checked in.
This could also contain a feature to post the NET report on the internet with the push of a button if so desired.
Marquee
New Marquee
This feature will allow NCS stations to transmit a new message and color for the top of the CommStat scrolling marquees.
Any group station that hears the message will automatically update the color and message of their marquee.
Marquee encoding
New Marquee
This feature will allow NCS stations to transmit a new message and color for the top of the CommStat scrolling
marquees.
Any group station that hears the message will automatically update the color and message of their marquee.
Marquee String encoding :
Callsign Group Color Reason for level Message Type Identifier
Typical marquee string : KD8PGB: @AMRRON ,0,NO IMMINENT THREATS AT THIS TIME,{*%} ?
Color encoding = 0 Green , 1 Yellow , 2 Red
Flash Bulletin
Flash Bulletin
This will allow an NCS Station to send a flash bulletin to all group stations that will cause a popup to stay
popped up until the user closes it.
Possible future state : include a capability to request any bulletin from any group station. You would QUERY
BULLETINS from any station and the software at the other station would send the last 3 bulletin numbers
and your software would tell you that you are missing one and you could request the bulletin number from
the other station.
Flash Bulletin Encoding
Flash Bulletin
This will allow an NCS Station to send a flash bulletin to all group stations that will cause a popup to stay
popped up until the user closes it.
Possible future state : include a capability to request any bulletin from any group station. You would QUERY
BULLETINS from any station and the software at the other station would send the last 3 bulletin numbers
and your software would tell you that you are missing one and you could request the bulletin number from
the other station.
Flash Bulletin String encoding :
Callsign Group JS8Call MSG Flag Bulletin ID Bulletin Text Message Type Identifier
Typical bulletin string : KD8PGB: @AMRRON MSG ,7315,BETA TEST FLASH BULLETIN,{^%} ?
Mapping
Mapping
The map will auto populate with group members that have been heard using any type of directed
transmission.
Mapping is not limited to members, this is so you can see stations you might want to relay through.
Mapping does work offline but you need to use it online for the tiles to be downloaded. Then you will have
some mapping functionality when using it offline.
